metadata.name: BLOCK
metadata.comment: Records of all blocks that have occurred on Algorand, dating back to the genesis block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: Timestamp of block minting(without a timezone)

BLOCK_DATE.name: BLOCK_DATE
BLOCK_DATE.comment: Date of block minting(without a timezone)

REWARDS_LEVEL.name: REWARDS_LEVEL
REWARDS_LEVEL.comment: How many rewards, in MicroAlgos, have been distributed to each RewardUnit of MicroAlgos since genesis. Link: https://algorand.github.io/java-algorand-sdk/com/algorand/algosdk/v2/client/model/BlockRewards.html

NETWORK.name: NETWORK
NETWORK.comment: Signifying whether the block is from mainnet or testnet

GENESIS_HASH.name: GENESIS_HASH
GENESIS_HASH.comment: The hash of the genesis block of the network for which the transaction is valid

PREV_BLOCK_HASH.name: PREV_BLOCK_HASH
PREV_BLOCK_HASH.comment: ID to which the block before this belongs

TXN_ROOT.name: TXN_ROOT
TXN_ROOT.comment: TransactionsRoot authenticates the set of transactions appearing in the block. More specifically, it's the root of a merkle tree whose leaves are the block's Txids, in lexicographic order. For the empty block, it's 0. Note that the TxnRoot does not authenticate the signatures on the transactions, only the transactions themselves. Two blocks with the same transactions but in a different order and with different signatures will have the same TxnRoot.

HEADER.name: HEADER
HEADER.comment: Block details, see rules below- for more message details https://developer.algorand.org/docs/rest-apis/indexer/#blockrewards
